{"cursor":"30034","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n'Public economics' (or 'economics of the public sector') is the study of\ngovernment policy through the lens of economic efficiency and equity. At its\nmost basic level, public economics provides a framework for thinking about\nwhether or not the government should participate in economics markets and to\nwhat extent its role should be. In order to do so, microeconomic theory is\nutilized to assess whether the private market is likely to provide efficient\noutcomes in the absence of governmental interference. Inherently, this study\ninvolves the analysis of government taxation and expenditures. This subject\nencompasses a host of topics including market failures, externalities, and the\ncreation and implementation of government policy. Public economics builds on the\ntheory of welfare economics and is ultimately used as a tool to improve social\nwelfare. Serge-Christophe Kolm, 1987. \"public economics,\" [[The New\nPalgrave: A Dictionary of Economics]], v. 3, pp. 1047â55. [http://www.dict-\nionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde1987_X001794&edition=all&field=content&q=\nTable of Contents.]\n\nBroad methods and topics include:\n* the theory and application of public finance â¢ Richard A. Musgrave, 2008.\n  \"public finance,\" The New Palgrave Dictionary of Economics, 2nd Edition. [htt-\n  p://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_P000244&edition=current&-\n  q= Abstract.]    â¢ _____, 1959.The Theory of Public Finance: A\n  Study in Public Economy''. J.M. Buchanan review,\n  [http://www.jstor.org/pss/1054956 1st page.]\n* analysis and design of public policy â¢ Dani Rodrik, 1996. \"Understanding\n  Economic Policy Reform,\" Journal of Economic Literature, 34(1), pp.\n  [http://relooney.fatcow.com/rodrik.pdf 9â41.] From [[The New Palgrave\n  Dictionary of Economics]] Online, 2008. Abstract links for:   \n  â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_B000331&edition=cu-\n  rrent&field=content&q= behavioural public economics\"] by B. Douglas Bernheim\n  and Antonio Rangel    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/-\n  article?id=pde2008_F000118&edition=all&field=content&q= \"fiscal federalism\"]\n  by David E. Wildasin    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.co-\n  m/article?id=pde2008_E000262&edition=all&field=content&q=analysis \"hazardous\n  waste, economics of\"] by Hilary Sigman.    â¢ [http://www.dicti-\n  onaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_N000165&edition=all&field=content&q=\n  \"nutrition and public policy in advanced economies\"] by Janet Currie.\n* distributional effects of taxation and government expenditures The New\n  Palgrave Dictionary of Economics, 2008, 2nd Edition. Abstract/contents links\n  for:   â¢\n  [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_P000244&edition=\n  \"public finance\"] by Richard A. Musgrave    â¢ [http://www.dict-\n  ionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_C000320&edition=current&q=\n  \"consumption taxation\"] by James M. Poterba    â¢ [http://www.d-\n  ictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_D000261&edition=all&field=content-\n  &q= \"distributive politics and targeted public spending\"] by Brian G.\n  Knight    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=p-\n  de2008_G000203&edition=current&q= \"generational accounting\"] by Jagadeesh\n  Gokhale    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=-\n  pde2008_N000165&edition=all&field=content&q= \"nutrition and public policy in\n  advanced economies\"] by Janet Currie    â¢ [http://www.dictiona-\n  ryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_P000218&edition=all&field=content&q=\n  \"progressive and regressive taxation\"] by William Vickrey and Efe A. Ok    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_R00-\n  0067&edition=current&q= \"redistribution of income and wealth\"] by F.A.\n  Cowell    â¢\n  [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_T000240&edition= \"tax\n  expenditures\"] by Daniel N. Shaviro    â¢ [http://www.dictionar-\n  yofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_T000236&edition=current&q= \"taxation and\n  poverty\"] by John Karl Scholz    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeco-\n  nomics.com/article?id=pde2008_W000053&edition=current&q= \"welfare state\"] by\n  Assar Lindbeck.    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/art-\n  icle?id=pde2008_S000525&edition=all&field=content&q= social insurance and\n  public policy] by Jonathan Gruber.\n* analysis of market failure The New Palgrave Dictionary of Economics, 2008,\n  2nd Edition. Abstract links for:    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryof-\n  economics.com/article?id=pde2008_M000056&edition=current&q= \"market failure\"]\n  by John O. Ledyard    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/-\n  article?id=pde2008_B000237&edition=current&field=content&q= \"bureaucracy\"] by\n  Mancur Olson    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/articl-\n  e?id=pde2008_E000228&edition=current&field=content&q= \"health insurance,\n  economics of\"] by Joseph P. Newhouse    â¢ [http://www.dictiona-\n  ryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_P000360&edition=all&field=content&q=\n  \"mandated employer provision of employee benefits\"] by Jonathan Gruber    â¢ [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_P00-\n  0245&edition=current&field=content&q= \"public goods\"] by Agnar Sandmo\n  and government failure. â¢ Sharun W. Mukand, 2008. \"policy reform,\n  political economy of,\" The New Palgrave Dictionary of Economics 2nd Edition.\n  [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_P000363&edition=curr-\n  ent&q= Abstract.]    â¢ James M. Buchanan, 2008. \"public debt,\"\n  The New Palgrave Dictionary of Economics 2nd Edition. [http://www.dictionaryo-\n  feconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_P000241&edition=current&q= Abstract.]    â¢ Mrinal Datta-Chaudhuri, 1990. \"Market Failure and Government\n  Failure,\" Journal of Economic Perspectives, 4(3) , pp.\n  [http://netdrive.montclair.edu/~lebelp/DattaChaudMktFailJEP1990.pdf 25-\n  39.].    â¢ Kenneth J. Arrow, 1969. \"The Organization of\n  Economic Activity: Issues Pertinent to the Choice of Market versus Non-market\n  Allocations,\" in Analysis and Evaluation of Public Expenditures: The PPP\n  System. Washington, D.C., Joint Economic Committee of Congress. PDF reprint as\n  pp. [http://www.econ.ucsb.edu/~tedb/Courses/UCSBpf/readings/ArrowNonMktActivi-\n  ty1969.pdf 1-16] (press '+').    â¢ Joseph E. Stiglitz, 2009.\n  \"Regulation and Failure,\" in David Moss and John Cisternino (eds.), New\n  Perspectives on Regulation, ch. 1, pp.\n  [http://www.tobinproject.org/twobooks/pdf/New_Perspectives_Ch1_Stiglitz.pdf\n  11-23.] Cambridge: The Tobin Project.\n\nEmphasis is on analytical and scientific methods and normative-ethical analysis,\nas distinguished from ideology. Examples of topics covered are tax\nincidence, Gilbert E. Metcalf, 2008. \"tax incidence,\" The New Palgrave\nDictionary of Economics, 2nd Edition. [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/art-\nicle?id=pde2008_T000019&edition=current&q= Abstract.] optimal\ntaxation, Louis Kaplow, 2008. \"optimal taxation,\" The New Palgrave\nDictionary of Economics, 2nd Edition. [http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/art-\nicle?id=pde2008_O000034&edition=current&q= Abstract.] and the theory of\npublic goods. â¢ Agnar Sandmo, 2008.\"public goods,\" The\nNew Palgrave Dictionary of Economics, 2nd Edition.\n[http://www.dictionaryofeconomics.com/article?id=pde2008_P000245&edition=\nAbstract.]    â¢ Serge-Christophe Kolm, 1987. \"public economics,\"\nThe [[New Palgrave: A Dictionary of Economics]], v. 3, pp. 1047-48.    â¢ Anthony B. Atkinson and Joseph E. Stiglitz, 1980. Lectures in\nPublic Economics, McGraw-Hill, pp. vii-xi.    â¢ Mancur Olson,\n1971, 2nd ed.The Logic of Collective Action: Public Goods and the Theory of\nGroups, Harvard University Press, [http://books.google.com/books?id=jzTeOLtf7_w-\nC&dq=frontcover&source=bn&hl=en&ei=MEbjSfrNEaHUlQf8lsDgD